    <text>
        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
          <p><addressee>Mr. <sic>Isaach</sic> Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p>Minister of the Congregation</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Mikveh Israel</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p><add><hi rend="underline">Yiddish</hi></add></p> 
          <p rend="indent(9)"><placeName>N. Y.</placeName> <date><hi rend="underline">Friday</hi>&#44; Pericope Matoh<add>&#63;</add></date></p>
          <p rend="indent(9)"><date>&#40;June&#41;&#44; 1849</date></p>
			<p>Peace&#44; etc&#44; etc&#44; to my friend <addressee>Rabbi Isaac</addressee>&#58;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Yesterday I received your letter and do not delay<lb/> to reply to you in accordance with your wish. With<lb/> regard to the Torah&#44; which I am writing at your order&#44;<lb/> herewith call your attention to the fact that it is almost<lb/> half done. I am really diligent in this work&#44; and if God<lb/> grant me health&#44; I expect to finish it in five or six<lb/> weeks. I have been occupied with a variety of things I cann<add>&#63;</add><lb/> mention here and celebrated the completion of the Torah&#44; upon<lb/> which I was working when you were here&#44; only last <date>Shabu<lb/>oth</date>. I hope to God&#44; and thank him&#44; that everyone is well in<lb/> my family. That of course&#44; is the most important matter<lb/> I hope the same is true in your case&#44; and in the case of<lb/> those who are yours.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I have a proposition for you. <persName>Mr. Kurschitt</persName> saw the<lb/> Torah which you had. I looked through it and found it<lb/> Kosher. I made new &#8220;Etz&#45;claims&#8221;&#42; for it and it is now con<lb/>siderably lighter. I have the authority to sell it. If you&#44; a<lb/> any time&#44; have need for it&#44; you might turn to me. If not<lb/> have the kindness to recommend me in the &#8220;Occident&#8221;</p>
			<p>1&#8212;as scribe&#44; to write new Torahs&#44; with respect to which I<lb/> show excellent recommendations&#44; I have written seve<add>&#63;</add><lb/> and the people have been very much satisfied with them<lb/> well as with my T&#39;phillim and Mezzot<add>&#63;</add>.</p>
			<p>2&#8212;that I have at hand two excellent Torahs&#44; one big one<lb/> and one twenty inches long. Also all kinds of books&#44;<lb/> prayer books for <date>Rosh Hashonah</date> printed in <placeName>Furth</placeName>&#44; <placeName>Albach</placeName>&#44;<lb/> and <placeName>Vienna</placeName>. Also prayer books&#44; pentateuchs of all<lb/> kinds&#44; German and Polish ritual. Also very good woolen<lb/> and silk Talithum.</p>
			<p>&#42;rollers.</p>
		<pb n="4"/>
			<p>That how you might present this in the shortest and<lb/> best way. I need not tell you. Since you <del>see what<lb/> I have through my</del> yourself are convinced of my<lb/> ability as a scribe you will know how to recommend<lb/> one. Whatever expense this will involve&#44; I will gladly<lb/> pay. With best wishes&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)">Sincerely yours&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">Notta</persName>&#44; son of <persName>Isaac Dov</persName></p>
			<p>Scribe</p>
			<p>N.B.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I want to let you know something new. <persName>Mr.<lb/> Frank</persName>&#44; a printer&#44; is having prayer books printed<lb/> with an English translation just like your<lb/> prayer books in Octavo. This obviously will decre<add>&#63;</add><lb/> your sale. He set the price of &#36;1. each&#44; which will <add>&#63;</add><lb/> our sales a bit weak. This I let you know&#44; not as a<lb/> matter of gossip&#44; God forbid. However&#44; I beg of you<lb/> not to reveal who told you.</p>

          
        </body>
